The paper deals with matroidal networks and their relationship with scalar-linear solvability, which involves linear algebraic techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing. The paper also involves matroid theory, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control), respectively. Finally, the paper involves network theory, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
